{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"cd2f3bf1-691b-4f56-a2bb-8df35b81c4c4","content":"Your project is set up correctly. The `IsValidEmail` method is missing the `@` check, causing `Validate_MissingAtSign_ReturnsFalse` to fail.\n\nTo use **HotReload** for fast iteration, run:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test -- --hotreload\n```\n\nThis starts the test runner in hot-reload mode — it watches for file changes and **automatically re-runs tests** when you save, without a full rebuild. The `--` separates `dotnet test` args from testing-platform args.\n\n**Workflow:**\n1. Start the command above in a terminal\n2. Edit `IsValidEmail` in `EmailValidatorTests.cs` (e.g., add `&& email.Contains(\"@\")`)\n3. Save — tests re-run automatically\n4. Repeat until all tests pass\n5. Press `Ctrl+C` to exit\n\nThis is much faster than running `dotnet test` repeatedly since it skips the full build/restore cycle on each iteration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a7ccd858-3d89-405a-b88f-ff106ad24da8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has the HotReload extension already referenced. They want to know how to use it to quickly iterate on test fixes.\n\nLooking at the tests:\n1. `Validate_ValidEmail_ReturnsTrue` - passes (non-empty string with @)\n2. `Validate_MissingAtSign_ReturnsFalse` - FAILS because `IsValidEmail(\"userexample.com\")` returns `true` (it's not empty), but the test expects `false`\n3. `Validate_EmptyString_ReturnsFalse` - passes\n\nThe `IsValidEmail` method only checks for null/empty but doesn't check for `@`.\n\n\nTo use HotReload for iterating on fixes, I'd run the test project with the `--hotreload` flag or use `dotnet watch test`, which watches for code changes and automatically re-runs the tests without needing to restart the process.","outputTokens":706,"requestId":"5C33:8AA5A:1FDE869:2460491:69F5544B"},"id":"f9fd2489-4553-45a7-949e-c8f6027afd45","timestamp":"2026-05-02T01:33:15.655Z","parentId":"0cf1a067-efb2-4857-9202-e7e21fc1b753"}
